    "body": "This pull request adds a safeguard to the `grouped_topk` function in `fused_moe.py` to ensure correct behavior when the number of experts does not meet the requirements for grouped top-k computation. If the conditions are not met, the function now logs a warning and falls back to the standard top-k computation.\n\nNote:\n- This PR is required to resolve the following test on ROCm:\n    - `pytest -s -v tests/v1/e2e/test_spec_decode.py::test_mtp_correctness[deepseek]`\n- The issue also occurs on cuda if  `envs.VLLM_USE_FUSED_MOE_GROUPED_TOPK` is not used\n\ne.g. For the following model used in `tests/v1/e2e/test_spec_decode.py`\n- `ZixiQi/DeepSeek-V3-4layers-MTP-FP8`\n    - \"n_group\": 8,\n    - \"n_routed_experts\": 8,\n\nWithout this PR we get the following error:\n>   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/vllm/model_executor/layers/fused_moe/fused_moe.py\", line 1209, in torch_dynamo_resume_in_grouped_topk_at_1205\n    scores.view(num_token, num_expert_group, -1).topk(2, dim=-1)[0].sum(dim=-1)\n    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nRuntimeError: selected index k out of range\n\n",
    "created_at": "2025-11-25T19:57:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-01-20T22:59:48Z",
